	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=26464&amp;mid=10792604012242">Manageable hate</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=26464&amp;mid=10792604012242#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Sun, Mar 14th 5:33 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=157153"><span id="Scholar">aanil</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">28 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.99]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;My ranger wields this as primary...  And I love my toothpick!<br/><br/>  I have very little trouble with aggro when the meatshield is an experienced elemental/time geared warrior or reasonably well equipped and competent knight.  Clueless pl'd warriors in pickups groups with no anger/eb items are a different story, but I'd peel mobs off them wielding fine steel - it's kinda hard not to if you're oor anytime you try to stand behind them...<br/><br/>  My offhand is a Stone Etched Mallet which procs rune 2, also considered a high aggro proc.  Aggro theft is a non-issue for me.  Of course..  our raids usually have skilled, well equipped tanks who are very good at generating hate, and there are not to many Warriors doing Earth and Fire XP groups who don't have a few nice hate makers in their bags.  Your mileage may vary, adjust to your tank..  Bag something not quite so nasty for those times your tank just plain sucks.  Pulling out Swiftwind or your old Honorable Longsword is always a nice subtle way to tell your tank what you think of them.<br/><br/>  You have to be reasonable about it and employ normal aggro control tools (delayed engage, proper melee range, spaced nuking, and due consideration for anything you snared or pulled) - and you need tanks who know that there's more to holding aggro than smacking the mob around a little.  But at this level of the game (I expect this to be farmed by elemental raid forces, though some VT/Tier 3 forces might could pull it off), you know how to manage hate and have some decent meatshields to hide behind - or you'll die all the time no matter what weapons you have.<br/><br/>  As for the Stave...  It makes a great DPS weapon alternative to many of the equivelent or marginally better elementals weapons, which haven't dropped as often as I'd like.  Based on my experience tanking with the toothpick, I would not recommend it for a Warrior except as a DPS/Secondary tool - easily available Obsidian Shatter weapons are much better for 1H hate generation.  The stave would be decent with an Anger aug if nothing better (read: +hate/stun/debuff proc) is available, but really is not a first choice for pissing mobs off.<br/></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />[65 Forest Stalker] Aanil &lt;Infinit&gt;<br/></td></tr>
